EVENT_NAME: Community Conversation: "What is the difference between tokenization and inclusion?"
TEXT:
Take the opportunity to sit down with your neighbors and chat about what you’d like to see in your neighborhood over a cup of coffee! NWNW’s Community Café Conversations (C3) provide a prompt for lively conversation about what diversity, equity, and inclusion means to you and your neighborhood. Grab your beverage of choice and join us via Zoom! 

The conversation topic for May is, “What is the difference between tokenization and inclusion?”

See www.nwnw.org/calendar for zoom link
contact for meeting access president@northwestdistrictassociation.org

EVENT_NAME: SE Uplift Land Use & Transportation Committee meeting
TEXT:
The monthly SE Uplift Land Use and Transportation Committee (LUTC) meeting welcomes all residents, community organizations, and neighborhood Land Use/Transportation Representatives. 
We hear from content experts on a variety of land use and transportation related topics, network, and keep in tune to projects happening in Southeast and across Portland. 
The LUTC meets the third Monday of every month except in August and December. Contact Leah Fisher, Neighborhood Planning Program Manager if you'd like to request/propose an agenda item.

LOCATION: Carvlin Hall, St Philip Neri Campus, 2408 SE 16th Ave
TEXT:
Hosford Abernethy Neighborhood Development meets on the third Tuesday of the month at 7 PM, St. Phillip Neri Church, 2408 SE 16th Avenue.

No meetings in August and December.
